						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1449 (1527 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Gives the genealogy of the chief as: <hi rend="bold">Kōbaḷa,</hi> his son <hi rend="bold">Tippaya,</hi> his son <hi rend="bold">Vasava,</hi> his sons, the donors. Registers a gift of the village Guhapriyam by the sons of <hi rend="bold">Vasavayya-Nāyaka</hi> of Kōbaḷa family out of their gratitude to god Raṅganātha who favoured their father with eternal bliss (<hi rend="italic">Vaikuṇṭhaprāpti</hi>) (see No. 383 above). A share of the offerings is allotted to <hi rend="italic">Kandāḍai-Nāyaṉtirumāḷigai</hi> towards the feeding of <hi rend="italic">Śrīvaishṇavas.</hi> Only the <hi rend="bold">Śaka year 1449</hi> expressed by the chronogram <hi rend="italic">Dhanvibhōgyē</hi> is preserved, the other details of the date being lost. </p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
